claim.claim-text:
29. A method of inspecting a workpiece, comprising the acts of: 
providing the workpiece; 
projecting an array of charged particle beams towards the workpiece; 
passing each of the beams through one of a plurality of pole pieces, there being one pole piece associated with each beam, and through a single lens coil surrounding the plurality of pole pieces; 
detecting resulting secondary or backscattered particles from the workpiece; and 
determining a presence or absence of defects in the workpiece from the detected particles.
